reviews.review: The packed theater I was in was dead quiet throughout and everyone rushed to leave when it ended. It might be the worst saga film.
I loved it. The only disappointing things about this movie is that the Skywalker saga is over, and all the negativity from people's opinions.

I am a life time Star Wars Fan, at 42 years old, I take the films as they are, It was great to see 3 more movies from Disney.
I loved the moving touch with Leia in this one, I had tears, I was happy and sad that this is the End, I think alot of people are kicking up because they think they can do better.
Great Movie, need to see it again, no real slow bits all fast pacing.
Go with a open view that it is a Movie not something to be pulled apart.
I simply can't believe how bad this movie is. I was literally rolling my eyes at the cringe and bad writing. This movie and entire trilogy should have never been made!
> TLJ at least, eliciting the *full one star, but it was painted into a corner and destined to be bad
why were they in such a rush? slow down.

I found it a little choppy at first, but thought that as it went on it picked up steam. It tied up loose ends and had some plot details that added depth to both the original trilogy and prequels that more casual fans will not notice. I felt more connection to the characters than I did in 7 or 8.

Having given this a second viewing, I'm of the opinion that TROS does close out the series for me, though it still does leave a lot of unanswered questions. Some from the earlier films and some raised within this movie.

Did I enjoy it? Absolutely. Is it Star Wars? Definitely.

It felt like Star Wars. I appreciate that. I like how they weren't afraid to go into mythos. The pacing was a bit rushed but this makes sense given that this movie had to follow a movie that tore the story apart and left Episode 9 with nothing to work with. The Force powers were a bit overboard. But I liked it. I liked that it felt right. I liked a lot of it.

Maybe I just love star wars but I liked it. There were certain problems with retcons but that's basically par for the course  for star wars movies if we're being honest. There was a lot of fan service that was a bit cringy but also a lot of it did hit for me. The finale of the film was pretty amazing overall.
